{"questionId":"9067311","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the mass of aspirin which reacted with 16.25 cm<sup>3</sup> of 0.100 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> NaOH solution.</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">n(aspirin) «= n(NaOH) =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{16}}{\\text{.25 c}}{{\\text{m}}^3}}}{{1000}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>16</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>.25 c</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>m</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> × 0.100 mol dm<sup>–3</sup> » = 1.625 × 10<sup>–3</sup> «mol»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">m(aspirin) «= 1.625 × 10<sup>–3</sup> mol × 180.17 g mol<sup>–1</sup> » = 0.293 «g»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong> Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067311","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.b(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the mass of aspirin which reacted with 16.25 cm3 of 0.100 mol dm−3 NaOH solution.","paper":"3","level":"sl","questionNumber":"b(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.2 Aspirin and penicillin","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}